<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: INGLEWOOD; BASKETBALL 
GAME CANCELED BECAUSE OF ROBBERY PROBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A basketball game between ninth-graders from Inglewood and Santa Monica high 
schools was canceled Friday, two weeks after a pair of Santa Monica High 
basketball players reported being robbed of their Walkman radios in Inglewood 
High's gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
 The boys basketball game, scheduled to be held in the Inglewood High gym, was 
canceled because an investigation of the alleged robbery had not been 
completed, said Sandor Rosenfield, an assistant principal at Santa Monica 
High.Rosenfield said the school plans to take part in all its future athletic 
events at Inglewood, however. 
</P>
<P>
 "This was an isolated incident that could have happened anywhere," Rosenfield 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbery occurred Jan. 26 when Santa Monica's junior varsity basketball 
squad played Inglewood High's team in Inglewood. Two Santa Monica high players 
reported that three people followed them into a gymnasium restroom and forced 
them at gunpoint to hand over their radios. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident is being investigated by Inglewood High campus police, who 
declined to comment Friday. Though Santa Monica High's ninth-grade basketball 
game at Inglewood was canceled, varsity and junior varsity games that the two 
schools were scheduled to play at Santa Monica High on Friday were set to go 
ahead as planned. 
</P>
