<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL; SANTA MARIA VALLEY CHRISTIAN GUARD SETS RECORD: 89 
POINTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chad Bickley, a six-foot junior point guard for Santa Maria Valley Christian 
Academy, scored a CIF Southern Section record 89 points -- including a record 
20 three-point shots -- to lead the Lions to a 130-48 Coast Valley League 
victory over Cuyama Valley on Friday night at Cuyama Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Bickley's 89 points shattered the previous record, which was set by Nick 
Tenneriello of Colbert in a game against Brentwood in the 1967-1968 season, by 
15 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Bickley made 20 of 32 three-point attempts to break the previous record of 14, 
set by Joe Phears of Pomona in a game against Bassett in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Bickley also broke the record for three-point baskets in a season. His 150 
this season breaks the previous record of 140, set by Steve Clover of Rolling 
Hills in the 1989-90 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Overall, Bickley made 27 of 48 shots from the field and 15 of 16 from the 
free-throw line. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Maria Valley Christian Academy, 20-3 overall and 8-0 in Coast Valley 
play, is a private school of 72 students. Stan Bickley, Chad's father, is the 
coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Cuyama Valley is 4-14, 1-7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
