to give Edison a 67-65 double-overtime victory over Servite in a boys' 
basketball game Friday night at Servite High. 
</P>
<P>
 They were Baird's only points of the game.Micah Kroeger led the Chargers with 
20 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison trailed by 15 points with four minutes left in the third quarter, but 
outscored Servite, 17-12, in the third quarter and, 16-6, in the fourth. Ben 
Beard had 16 points and 11 rebounds for the Chargers, who finished in a 
fourth-place tie with Ocean View. The teams will meet for the league's final 
playoff spot at 7 tonight at Fountain Valley High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Kris Valls had 20 points and teammate David Downs added 18 for Servite (17-8, 
10-4), which finished third. 
</P>
