<TEXT>
<P>
 Playing without key player Ali Ton and plagued by fouls early, No. 2-ranked 
Los Alamitos was upset, 60-45, by Katella in an Empire League boys' basketball 
game Friday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 The Griffins (21-4, 9-1) started hot, taking a 30-23 halftime lead, but 
Katella's defense shut them down in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella's Mike Pahl and LaBroyn Clayton came alive in the second half, Pahl 
scoring nine of his 14 points and Clayton 16 of his 22. Both finished with 10 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Staniec and Jeremy Vandervoet, two of Los Alamitos' top players, fouled 
out in the first half, and Ton was unable to play because of an ankle injury 
suffered last week. 
</P>
