<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST WINS, CLINCHES CONFERENCE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West made 35 of 39 free throws to beat Saddleback, 91-68, and clinch 
its fifth consecutive Orange Empire Conference women's basketball title Friday 
at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 67th consecutive home victory for the Rustlers (28-4, 10-1 in 
conference), the state's No. 2 team. 
</P>
<P>
 Kristin Brun and Nicole Quinn each were eight of eight on free throws. Julie 
Murdent, who had a game-high 18 points, made four of four. Murdent also had 11 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Feniello had a team-high 14 points for Saddleback (7-16, 2-9). 
</P>
</TEXT>
