<TEXT>
<P>
 Medical Device Firm Curtails Operations: Cardiac Science Inc., which has 
become known more for its role in the recent ICN Pharmaceuticals Inc. imbroglio 
than for its automatic heart defibrillator, said it has shut down engineering 
operations but will continue to be operated by its president. The Irvine 
research and development company, which has no revenue and lost $1.1 million in 
the first nine months of last year, is struggling to raise $5 million as it 
seeks federal approval to continue testing its defibrillator, which 
automatically sends an electrical shock to the heart when in senses cardiac 
arrest. Howard K. Cooper, the company's president and now its only employee, 
was part of dissident ICN shareholder Rafi Khan's failed bid to unseat Milan 
Panic as ICN chairman. 
