<HEADLINE>
<P>
T-SHIRT PRICE NOT EXACTLY RIGHT FOR OLYMPIC CHIEF SAMARANCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE KUPPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Juan Antonio Samaranch, president of the International Olympic Committee, was 
outbid for the final countdown T-shirt in downtown Lillehammer. 
</P>
<P>
 Harald Belsvik, a local businessman, has been auctioning a T-shirt a day for 
the last three years, starting with one that said "1,000 days left till the 
Olympics," turning the proceeds over to the Lillehammer Olympic Organizing 
Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday's said "1 day left till the Olympics," and went for 56,000 Norwegian 
kroner -- more than $7,500 -- to Arthur Buchardt, a businessman. Samaranch 
dropped out of the bidding at 50,000 kroner. MIKE KUPPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021294-0138 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 012765 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 12, 1994, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
