<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forward Sean Elliott of the Detroit Pistons apparently will be cleared to play 
in Tuesday night's game against the Washington Bullets. 
</P>
<P>
 An examination of Arizona's University Medical Center cleared Elliott, who has 
a kidney ailment, to play after doctors in Detroit and Houston had disagreed. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Western Athletic Conference announced one-game suspensions for John Fish 
of Brigham Young and Carlus Groves of San Diego State for fighting during 
Thursday's game at Provo, Utah. Names in the News 
</P>
<P>
 Will Lemki, manager of German soccer league champion Werder Bremen, said he 
had been a double agent for West Germany and the Soviet KGB in the 1970s and 
'80s. 
</P>
