<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK SPLITS MANAGERS FOR EXPANSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hollywood Park has restructured its management team into two divisions to 
accommodate expanding racing operations and expansion into gaming and 
entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 Track President Don Robbins was named president of the racing operations 
division, and G. Michael Finnigan, executive vice president and chief financial 
officer, will also be president of gaming and entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 Eual G. Wyatt, longtime racing secretary, was promoted to general manager, and 
a search is underway to find a new racing secretary. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
